                            <comment id="94089" author="olivergierke" created="Tue, 1 Oct 2013 07:17:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve created &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATACMNS-376&quot; title=&quot;Repositories cannot deal with CGLib proxied classes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DATACMNS-376&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DATACMNS-376&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and am about to commit a fix for it as I write this. I&apos;d still like to add a test case to Spring Data REST to guard against regressions here. Am I right in the assumption, that &lt;tt&gt;Picture&lt;/tt&gt; is an embedded object in &lt;tt&gt;Category&lt;/tt&gt; or is it one that&apos;s linked to?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
